info.description:
The Reference Data is prerequisite global data which is meant to be used in the other services. This API is 
utilised by both the Deals API and the Quotes API as well as being externally available for consumption.

All Date Times in the BSL are defined as EPOCH times.  Unix time (also known as POSIX time or Epoch time) is a system for describing instants in time, defined as the number of seconds that have elapsed since 00:00:00 Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), Thursday, 1 January 1970, not counting leap seconds.
All programming languages support this nativley.  A converter can be found here: http://www.epochconverter.com/
